  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(7) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "If ye endure chastening.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The whole weight of ancient evidence is in favour of a change in the first Greek word. Two translations are then possible: (1) “It is for chastening that ye endure:” the troubles that come upon you are for discipline—are not sent in anger, but in fatherly love. (2) “Endure for chastening:” bear the trial, instead of seeking to avoid it by unworthy and dangerous concession; endure it, that it may effect its merciful purpose.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "What son is he.—Or, what son is there whom his father chasteneth not?",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "What son is he.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Or, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "what son is there whom his",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " father chasteneth ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "not?",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
