  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 7, 8.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "For chastening ye endure",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "It is for chastening that ye endure.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The reading ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "εἰς παιδείαν ὑπομένετε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", supported by almost the whole weight of manuscripts (including all the uncials that contain the text), of ancient versions, and commentators (Theophylact being the only certain exception), is decidedly to be accepted instead of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "εἰ παιδείαν ὑπομένετε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (equivalent to \"if ye endure chastening\") of the Textus Receptus. Moreover, it is required for the sense of the passage in regard to the proper meaning of the verb ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ὑπομένετε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (\"endure\"), which is to \"submit to,\" or \"endure patiently,\" not simply \"to undergo.\" For to say, \"if ye endure chastisement patiently, God dealeth with you as sons,\" has no meaning; our being treated as sons depends, not on the way we take our chastisement, but on our being chastised at all. The use of the preposition ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "εἰς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " to express purpose is common in this Epistle (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 1:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "εἰς διακονίαν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": 3:5, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "εἰς μαρτύριον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": 4:16, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "εἰς βοήθειαν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": 6:16, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "εἰς βεβαίωσιν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): and the essential sense of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "παιδεία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is discipline or education. The drift is the same, whether we take ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ὑπομένετε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as an indicative or an imperative. Thus the next clause of the verse follows suitably: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "God dealeth with you as with sons; for what son is there",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (or, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "who is a son",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "whom his father chasteneth not? But if ye be without chastening, whereof all",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cmt_word",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "whom his father chasteneth not? But if ye be without chastening, whereof all",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (i.e. all God's children, with reference to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "have been made partakers, then are ye bastards, and not sons",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (ye are not your father's real children whom he cares for as such). Hebrews 12:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "If ye endure chastening (εἰς παιδείαν ὑπομένετε)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Rend. \"it is for chastening that ye endure.\" A.V. follows the reading of T. R. εἰ if. Do not faint at affliction. Its purpose is disciplinary. Παιδεία is here the end or result of discipline. In Hebrews 12:5 it is the process.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Rend. \"it is for chastening that ye endure.\" A.V. follows the reading of T. R. εἰ if. Do not faint at affliction. Its purpose is disciplinary. Παιδεία is here the end or result of discipline. In ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Hebrews 12:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " it is the process.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "God dealeth with you as with sons (ὡς υἱοῖς ὑμῖν προσφέρεται ὁ θεὸς)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The verb means to bring to: often to bring an offering to the altar, as Matthew 5:23, Matthew 5:24; Matthew 8:4. In the passive voice with the dative, to be born toward one; hence, to attack, assail, deal with, behave toward. See Thucyd. i. 140; Eurip. Cycl. 176; Hdt. vii. 6. The afflictive dealing of God with you is an evidence that you are sons.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "The verb means to bring to: often to bring an offering to the altar, as ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 5:23",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 5:24",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 8:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". In the passive voice with the dative, to be born toward one; hence, to attack, assail, deal with, behave toward. See Thucyd. i. 140; Eurip. Cycl. 176; Hdt. vii. 6. The afflictive dealing of God with you is an evidence that you are sons.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "What son is he whom the father, etc. (τίς υἰὸς)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Some interpreters render, \"who is a son whom the father?\" etc. That is, no one is a son who is without paternal chastening. The A.V. is better. The idea expressed by the other rendering appears in the next verse. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]